obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47498)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47498&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Lady Hardinge Medical College`
  line `and Hospital (Acquisition) and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1977.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st February, 1978, vide notification No. S. O. 188(E), dated 12th January, 1978, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47499)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47499&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date on which this Act comes into force;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board of Administration" means the Board of Administration constituted by the Central`
  line `Government under the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) "Board of Management" means the Board of Management of the Kalavati Saran Hospital,`
  line `constituted by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) "Fund" means the Lady Hardinge Hospital for Women and Children, Delhi, Fund`
  line `established by the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(e) "Kalavati Saran Hospital" means the institution known as the Kalavati Saran Childrens`
  line `Hospital, New Delhi, together with the dispensaries attached thereto and used in connection`
  line `therewith, and includes all laboratories and libraries used in connection with, or as accessories to, or`
  line `adjuncts of, the said Hospital;`
  line
  line `(f) "Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital" means the institutions known as the Lady`
  line `Hardinge Medical College for Women, New Delhi, and the Lady Hardinge Hospital for Women and`
  line `Children, New Delhi, together with the dispensaries attached thereto and used in connection`
  line `therewith, and includes all lecture-rooms, museums, laboratories, libraries, hostels and`
  line `boarding-houses used in connection with, or as accessories to, or adjuncts of, the said College of`
  line Hospital;
  line
  line `(g) "Scheme" means the Scheme for the administration of the Fund settled by the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Charitable Endowments Act, 1890 (6 of 1890),`
  line `and published with the notification of the Government of India, in the late Ministry of Health,`
  line `No. F. 4-3(1) /53-MI, dated the 12th June, 1953, as amended by the notifications of the Government`
  line `of India, in the late Ministry of Health, No. F. 4-77/56-MII, dated the 14th March, 1957 and`
  line `No. F. 4-77/56-MII, dated the 17th April, 1957;`
  line
  line `(h) "Treasurer" means the Treasurer of Charitable Endowments for India, appointed under the`
  line `Charitable Endowments Act, 1890 (6 of 1890).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47500)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital to vest in Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47500&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the`
  line `appointed day, the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital together with--`
  line
  line `(a) all lands, on which the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital stands, and all other`
  line `lands appurtenant thereto and all buildings, erections and fixtures on such lands;`
  line
  line `(b) all furniture, equipments, stores, apparatuses and appliances, drugs, moneys and other assets`
  line `of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital;`
  line
  line `(c) all other properties and assets, movable and immovable including leases pertaining to the`
  line `Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital, whether vested in the Treasurer of the Board of`
  line `Administration or in any other person; and all rights, powers, authorities and privileges, cash`
  line `balances, reserve funds, investments and all other rights and interests in, or in relation to, or arising`
  line `out of, such property as were, immediately before the appointed day, in the ownership, possession,`
  line `power or control of the Treasurer or the Board of Administration or any other person in charge of`
  line `the management of the affairs of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital; and`
  line
  line `(d) all borrowings made by, or on behalf of, and all other liabilities and obligations of whatever`
  line `kind, incurred in relation to, the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital, and subsisting on the`
  line `appointed day,`
  line
  line `shall stand transferred to, and shall vest absolutely in, the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every deed of gift, endowment, bequest or trust or other document in relation to all or any of the`
  line `properties, and assets, referred to in sub-section (1), shall, as from the appointed day, be construed as if it`
  line `were made or executed in favour of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, any property, referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), which, by virtue of the provisions of that sub-section, has vested in the Central`
  line `Government, shall, by force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation,`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien and other incumbrances affecting it, and any attachment, injunction or any decree`
  line `or order of any court or tribunal restricting the use of such property in any manner shall be deemed to`
  line `have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, any proceeding or cause of action, pending`
  line `or existing immediately before the appointed day, by or against the Treasurer or the Board of`
  line `Administration or any other person, in relation to the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital, may,`
  line `as from the appointed day, be continued and enforced by or against the Central Government as it might`
  line `have been enforced by or against the Treasurer or the Board of Administration or such other person if`
  line `this Act had not been enacted, and shall cease to be enforceable by or against the Treasurer or the Board`
  line `of Administration or such other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47501)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47501&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall give, in cash, to the Treasurer an amount`
  line `equivalent to the sum of rupees one lakh for the transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government, under`
  line `section 3, of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount, referred to in sub-section (1), shall be paid within three months from the appointed`
  line `day (hereafter in this section referred to as the specified period).`
  line
  line `(3) The amount, referred to in sub-section (1), if not paid within the specified period, shall carry`
  line `interest at the rate of four per cent. per annum from the date of expiry of the specified period until the`
  line `payment thereof`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47502)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital to be administered as Government institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47502&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital shall`
  line `be administered by the Central Government as a Government institution, and, in administering the`
  line `properties transferred to and vested in it under section 3, regard shall be had to the purposes specified in`
  line `the Scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47503)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Applicability of Act 2 of 1882 to Board of Administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47503&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `For the removal of doubts, it is`
  line `hereby declared that nothing in this Act shall be deemed to apply to any right accrued to, or any liability`
  line `incurred by, the Board of Administration or any member thereof under the provisions of the Indian Trusts`
  line `Act, 1882, in respect of anything done or omitted to be done by it or him during any period preceding the`
  line `appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47504)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Amount to be held for purposes of Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47504&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount paid under section 4 shall vest in`
  line `the Treasurer, and shall be held by him in the same manner as the Fund vested in him was held by`
  line `him immediately before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount paid to the Treasurer under section 4 shall be administered by the Board of`
  line `Administration in the same manner in which the Fund was administered by it, as if such amount were the`
  line Fund.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47505)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Kalavati Saran Hospital to be managed as Government institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47505&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any contract or instrument to the contrary, on and from the appointed day, the`
  line `Kalavati Saran Hospital shall be managed by the Central Government as a Government institution.`
  line
  line `(2) In managing the Kalavati Saran Hospital as a Government institution, regard shall be had to the`
  line `purposes for which that Hospital was set up in pursuance of the indenture, dated the 8th day of`
  line `June, 1954, executed by Shri Ashok Saran, and the indenture, dated the 8th day of June, 1954, executed`
  line `by Shri Raghbir Saran, in favour of the President of India.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the appointed day, the Board of Management shall stand dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (47506)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Act to override all other enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47506&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act or any decree or order of any court,`
  line `tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (47507)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Provisions relating to officers and other employees of Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital and Kalavati Saran Hospital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47507&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer or other employee, who, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, is employed in, or in connection with the affairs of, the Lady Hardinge Medical`
  line `College and Hospital, or, as the case may be, the Kalavati Saran Hospital, shall become, as from the`
  line `appointed day, an officer or other employee, as the case may be, of the Central Government, and shall`
  line `hold his office by the same tenure, at the same remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions and`
  line `with the same rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and other matters as he would have held, if this`
  line `Act had not been enacted, and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment under the Central`
  line `Government is duly terminated or until his remuneration, terms and conditions duly altered by the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the alteration so made is not acceptable to any such officer or other employee, his`
  line `employment may be terminated by the Central Government on payment to him of an amount equivalent`
  line `to three months' remuneration in the case of permanent employees and one month's remuneration in the`
  line `case of other employees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any officer or other`
  line `employee who has, by notice in writing given to the Central Government within thirty days next`
  line `following the appointed day, intimated his intention of not becoming an officer or other employee of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee,`
  line `employed in, or in connection with the affairs of, the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital or the Kalavati Saran Hospital to the Central Government shall not entitle any such officer or other`
  line `employee to any compensation under that Act, or any other law, and no such claim shall be entertained by`
  line `any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(3) For the persons who, immediately before the appointed day, were the trustees for any person,`
  line `provident or gratuity fund or any other like fund constituted for the officers or other employees of the`
  line `Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital and the Kalavati Saran Hospital, there shall be`
  line `substituted as trustees such persons as the Central Government may, by general or special order, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (47508)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Effect of contracts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47508&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) All contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers of attorney, grants`
  line `of legal representation and other instruments of whatever nature, subsisting or having effect immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, and to which the Board of Administration or, as the case may be, the Board of`
  line `Management, or any person on behalf of the Board of Administration or, as the case may be, the Board of`
  line `Management, is a party, or which are in favour of the Board of Administration or, as the case may be,`
  line `Board of Management, shall, in so far as they relate to any purpose, or affairs, of the Lady Hardinge`
  line `Medical College and Hospital, or, as the case may be, the Kalavati Saran Hospital, be of as full force and`
  line `effect against, or in favour of, the Central Government, and may be enforced or acted upon as full and`
  line `effectually as if in place of the Board of Administration or, as the case may be, the Board of`
  line `Management, the Central Government had been a party thereto or as if they had been issued in favour of`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature in relation to the`
  line `Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital, or, as the case may be, the Kalavati Saran Hospital, or any`
  line `affair of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital or the Kalavati Saran Hospital, is pending by,`
  line `or against, the Board of Administration or, as the case may be, the Board of Management or the Treasurer`
  line `or any other person, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be, in any way, prejudicially affected by`
  line `reason of the transfer of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital to the Central Government or`
  line `by reason of the assumption of management of the Kalavati Saran Hospital by the Central Government, or`
  line `of anything contained in this Act; but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be contained, prosecuted`
  line `and enforced by or against the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (47509)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Contracts, in bad faith or detrimental to the interests of Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital and Kalavati Saran Hospital to be cancelled or varied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47509&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 11, the Central Government may, if satisfied after such inquiry as it may think fit,`
  line `that any contract or agreement entered into before the appointed day between the Board of`
  line `Administration or Board of Management or any member thereof, in relation to the Lady Hardinge`
  line `Medical College and Hospital, or, as the case may be, the Kalavati Saran Hospital, or any affairs`
  line `connected with the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital or the Kalavati Saran Hospital, has been`
  line `entered into in bad faith, or is detrimental to the interests of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and`
  line `Hospital, or, as the case may be, the Kalavati Saran Hospital, it may make an order cancelling or varying`
  line `(either unconditionally or subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose for the purpose) such`
  line `contract or agreement and thereafter the contract or agreement shall have effect accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no contract or agreement shall be cancelled or varied except after giving to the parties`
  line `to the contract or agreement a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1), may make an application to the`
  line `principal court of civil jurisdiction within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the Lady Hardinge`
  line `Medical College and Hospital, or, as the case may be, the Kalavati Saran Hospital is situated, for the`
  line `variation or reversal of such order and thereupon such court may confirm, modify or reverse such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (47510)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Duty to deliver possession of property, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47510&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the transfer to, and the vesting in, the`
  line `Central Government of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital, and on the assumption of the`
  line `management of the Kalavati Saran Hospital by the Central Government,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of Administration, or, as the case may be, the Board of Management, and every`
  line `person in whose possession, custody or control any property or asset specified in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3, or any property or asset pertaining to the Kalavati Saran Hospital may be, shall deliver the`
  line `same to such officer or other person as may be authorised by the Central Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) the Board of Administration or, as the case may be, the Board of Management, and every`
  line `person who, immediately before such vesting or assumption, has in his possession, custody or control`
  line `any books, documents or other papers relating to the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital, or`
  line `the Kalavati Saran Hospital, shall be liable to account for the said books, documents and papers to`
  line `the Central Government and shall deliver them up to the Central Government or to such officer or`
  line `other person as may be authorised by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the other provisions contained in this section, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Central Government to take all necessary steps for taking possession of all properties and assets which`
  line `have been transferred to, and vested in, it under this Act, or in relation to which the management has been`
  line `assumed by it under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (47511)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47511&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property held for the purposes of the Lady`
  line `Hardinge Medical College and Hospital or the Kalavati Saran Hospital, wrongfully withholds such`
  line `property from the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of, or retains, any property held for the purposes of the Lady`
  line `Hardinge Medical College and Hospital, or the Kalavati Saran Hospital; or`
  line
  line `(c) willfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government any books, documents or`
  line `other papers relating to the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital or the Kalavati Saran`
  line `Hospital; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to deliver to the Central Government any assets, books or other documents in his`
  line `possession, custody or control relating to the Lady Hardinge Medical College and Hospital or the`
  line `Kalavati Saran Hospital; or`
  line
  line `(e) wrongfully removes or destroys any property held for the purposes of the Lady Hardinge`
  line `Medical College and Hospital or the Kalavati Saran Hospital; or`
  line
  line `(f) wrongfully uses any property held for the purposes of the Lady Hardinge Medical College and`
  line `Hospital or the Kalavati Saran Hospital,`
  line
  line `shall by punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (47512)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47512&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was reasonable`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (47513)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47513&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or any of its officers or other employees for anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (47514)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47514&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act except on a`
  line `complaint, in writing, made by the Central Government or any officer authorised in this behalf by that`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (47515)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47515&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every officer of the Central Government shall be indemnified by the Central`
  line `Government against all losses and expenses incurred by him in, or in relation to, the discharge of his`
  line `duties under this Act except such as have been caused by his own wilful act or default.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (47516)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130&sectionId=47516&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00005_197734_1517807320130
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
